template.template: SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0
template.name: SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0

trigger.expression: max(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/icmpping,#3)=0
trigger.name: Not Responding To ICMP
trigger.description: Last three attempts returned timeout. Please check device connectivity.

trigger.expression: min(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/icmppingloss,5m)>{$ICMP_LOSS_WARN} and min(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/icmppingloss,5m)<100
trigger.name: High ICMP Loss

dependency.name: Not Responding To ICMP
dependency.expression: max(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/icmpping,#3)=0

trigger.expression: avg(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/icmppingsec,5m)>{$ICMP_RESPONSE_TIME_WARN}
trigger.name: High ICMP Response Time

dependency.name: High ICMP Loss
dependency.expression: min(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/icmppingloss,5m)>{$ICMP_LOSS_WARN} and min(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/icmppingloss,5m)<100

dependency.name: Not Responding To ICMP
dependency.expression: max(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/icmpping,#3)=0

item.name: WAN Operational Status
item.description: The actual state of interfaces. Link can be Up(1), Down(2) or Unknown(3) state.

trigger.expression: (last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/integraEmodemBandwidth,#1)<>last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/integraEmodemBandwidth,#2))=1 and last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/integraEmodemBandwidth)>0
trigger.name: Bandwidth Changed

trigger.expression: (last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/integraEmodemErroredSecond,#1)<>last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/integraEmodemErroredSecond,#2))=1
trigger.name: Errored Seconds Increased

item.name: Modem Capacity Rx
item.description: Rx ethernet capacity in kilobits per second

trigger.expression: change(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/integraEmodemSeverelyErroredSecond)=1
trigger.name: Severely Errored seconds increased

item.name: Modem Capacity Tx
item.description: Tx ethernet capacity in kilobits per second

trigger.expression: last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/integraEsysCPUload)>80
trigger.name: High CPU Load

trigger.expression: (last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/LAN1_integraEifPortHighSpeed,#1)<>last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/LAN1_integraEifPortHighSpeed,#2))=1
trigger.name: LAN1 Port Speed Changed

item.name: LAN1 Operational Status
item.description: Actual state of interfaces. Link can be up(1), down(2) or in unknown(3) state.

trigger.expression: (last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/LAN2_integraEifPortHighSpeed,#1)<>last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/LAN2_integraEifPortHighSpeed,#2))=1
trigger.name: LAN2 Port Speed Changed

item.name: LAN2 Operational Status
item.description: Actual state of interfaces. Link can be up(1), down(2) or in unknown(3) state.

trigger.expression: (last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/LAN3_integraEifPortHighSpeed,#1)<>last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/LAN3_integraEifPortHighSpeed,#2))=1
trigger.name: LAN3 Port Speed Changed

item.name: LAN3 Operational Status
item.description: Actual state of interfaces. Link can be up(1), down(2) or in unknown(3) state.

item.name: System Contact Details
item.description: MIB: SNMPv2-MIB The textual identification of the contact person for this managed node, together with information on how to contact this person. If no contact information is known, the value is the zero-length string.

item.name: System Description
item.description: MIB: SNMPv2-MIB A textual description of the entity. This value should include the full name and version identification of the system's hardware type, software operating-system, and networking software.

item.name: System Location
item.description: MIB: SNMPv2-MIB The physical location of this node (e.g., `telephone closet, 3rd floor'). If the location is unknown, the value is the zero-length string.

item.name: System Hostname
item.description: MIB: SNMPv2-MIB An administratively-assigned name for this managed node.By convention, this is the node's fully-qualified domain name. If the name is unknown, the value is the zero-length string.

trigger.expression: (last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/system.name,#1)<>last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/system.name,#2))=1 and length(last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/system.name))>0
trigger.name: System Name Has Changed (New Name: {ITEM.VALUE})
trigger.description: System name has changed. Ack to close.

item.name: System Object ID
item.description: MIB: SNMPv2-MIB The vendor's authoritative identification of the network management subsystem contained in the entity. This value is allocated within the SMI enterprises subtree (1.3.6.1.4.1) and provides an easy and unambiguous means for determining`what kind of box' is being managed. For example, if vendor`Flintstones, Inc.' was assigned the subtree1.3.6.1.4.1.4242, it could assign the identifier 1.3.6.1.4.1.4242.1.1 to its `Fred Router'.

item.name: Uptime
item.description: MIB: SNMPv2-MIB The time since the network management portion of the system was last re-initialized.

trigger.expression: last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/system.uptime[sysUpTime.0])<10m
trigger.name: {HOST.NAME} Has Been Restarted (Uptime < 10m)

dependency.name: SNMP Not Available
dependency.expression: max(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/zabbix[host,snmp,available],{$SNMP.TIMEOUT})=0

item.name: SNMP Agent Availability
item.description: Availability of SNMP checks on the host. The value of this item corresponds to availability icons in the host list.

trigger.expression: max(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/zabbix[host,snmp,available],{$SNMP.TIMEOUT})=0
trigger.name: SNMP Not Available
trigger.description: SNMP is not available for polling. Please check device connectivity and SNMP settings.

dependency.name: Not Responding To ICMP
dependency.expression: max(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/icmpping,#3)=0

trigger.expression: last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/integraEifPortAdminStatus_LAN1)=1 and (last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/LAN1_integraEifPortOperStatus)=2 or last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/LAN1_integraEifPortOperStatus)=3)
trigger.name: LAN1 Port DOWN from Latest Data

trigger.expression: last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/integraEifPortAdminStatus_LAN2)=1 and (last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/LAN2_integraEifPortOperStatus)=2 or last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/LAN2_integraEifPortOperStatus)=3)
trigger.name: LAN2 Port DOWN from Latest Data

trigger.expression: last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/integraEifPortAdminStatus_LAN3)=1 and (last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/LAN3_integraEifPortOperStatus)=2 or last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/LAN3_integraEifPortOperStatus)=3)
trigger.name: LAN3 Port DOWN from Latest Data

trigger.expression: last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/integraEmodemModulation)<>last(/SAF Basic Integra-E template V1.1 for Zabbix 6.0/integraEmodemTxModulation)
trigger.name: Tx Modulation Differs From Configured Maximum
